{"id":19446,"date":"2014-07-02T18:14:15","date_gmt":"2014-07-02T14:14:15","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=19446"},"modified":"2019-05-20T15:54:34","modified_gmt":"2019-05-20T11:54:34","slug":"umar-not-sword-lash","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/02\/umar-not-sword-lash\/","title":{"rendered":"Umar II on Justice: People are fit for justice, not sword and lash"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Sa\u2019ib ibn Muhammad reported: Jarrah ibn Abdullah wrote to Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, saying, \u201cPeace be upon you. To proceed: The people of Khorasan have become unruly to govern. Indeed, they are fit for nothing but the sword and the lash. If the leader of the believers gives me permission, I will enact this policy.\u201d Umar wrote back to him saying, \u201cPeace be upon you. To proceed: I have been informed of your letter in which you said the people of Khorasan have become unruly and they are fit for nothing but the sword and the lash, and you have asked me to give you permission. You have lied. Rather, they are fit for justice and their rights, so enact that among them. Peace be upon you.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Ta\u0304ri\u0304kh Dimashq 26563<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0626\u0628 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u062f \u0643\u062a\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0631\u0627\u062d \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647 \u0625\u0644\u0649 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0643 \u0623\u0645\u0627 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0641\u0625\u0646 \u0623\u0647\u0644 \u062e\u0631\u0627\u0633\u0627\u0646 \u0642\u0648\u0645 \u0642\u062f \u0633\u0627\u0621\u062a \u0631\u0639\u064a